Virgin set to launch internet service in November . Richard Branson ' s Virgin Group is set to launch an Internet service in November in a joint venture with US cable firm International CableTel Inc . A Virgin company spokesman told Reuters , " We are going to offer a very consumer focused Internet service . We think there are an awful lot of people out there who have got PCs but there are not that many at home who use the internet . " He said the official launch of the service , to be known as Virgin Net , and details of the service would be announced in early November . Virgin Net is 51 percent owned by Virgin Communications with the remainder held by CableTel . RM Plc , which supplies information technology solutions to educational markets , said earlier Monday it had agreed with Virgin Net to provide an education service to home users via the Internet . - - London Newsroom + 44 171 542 4019 
